A head which does not require the system to be drained is identified by a small round bump on the cover and a 6 or higher OS suffix number. Only two screws and two locating pegs are used to connect heads to the body.

Title: Watts Industries Electro Controls ELF-3 water flow switch
Description: This Watts Industries Electro Controls ELF 230 VAC liquid flow switch detects liquid flow through chillers, boilers, pipes and other units to monitor pump operation or switch alarms in the event of flow failure. It is suitable for use with hot water, chilled water, diesel oil and up to 30% glycol systems.
